# Protos Web — Cursor AI Rules
# =============================
# Coding standards for Cursor AI. Canonical always-on rules: `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`
# Stack reference: `docs/architecture.md` · deploy: `docs/cursor-stack.md`

## Project Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router) with `src/` directory · React 19
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with CSS custom properties (`src/app/globals.css`)
- **Animations**: Framer Motion — GSAP is NOT installed
- **3D**: React Three Fiber (`@react-three/fiber`, `@react-three/drei`, `three`) — NOT vanilla Three.js outside R3F
- **Smooth scroll**: `lenis` (via LenisProvider)
- **State**: `zustand` where shared client state is needed
- **DOM + Canvas layers**: `.cursor/rules/dom-canvas-layers.mdc` — mandatory for UI/3D work
- **i18n**: `next-intl` — 6 locales: hr, en, de, it, es, sr (default: hr)
- **Icons**: `lucide-react` only
- **Backend**: Supabase only (Postgres, RLS, Storage, Edge Functions) — no Prisma, Convex, Firebase
- **Deploy**: `git push origin main` → GitHub CI + Vercel auto-deploy — never Vercel CLI
- **Admin secret**: `ADMIN_SECRET` on Vercel only — see `docs/security.md`

## File Structure
- Pages: `src/app/[locale]/` (+ `src/app/api/`, admin under `[locale]/admin/`)
- Components: `src/components/` — `features/`, `layout/`, `navigation/`, `providers/`, `three/`, `ui/`, `showcase/`, `legal/`, `seo/`
- Lib: `src/lib/` — `auth/`, `config/`, `queries/`, `routes/`, `showcase/`, `supabase/`
- Hooks: `src/hooks/`
- Types: `src/types/`
- Server actions: `src/actions/` (admin-*, contact)
- Messages: `src/messages/{locale}.json` (all 6 locales)
- Supabase: `supabase/migrations/`, `supabase/functions/` — coordinate with live remote before new migrations

## Component Rules
1. **`'use client'`** when using hooks, Framer Motion, browser APIs, R3F, or event handlers.

2. **R3F components MUST**:
   - Use `@react-three/fiber` + `@react-three/drei`
   - Dynamic import with `next/dynamic` and `{ ssr: false }`
   - Wrap in `<Canvas>` (or project `SafeCanvas` wrapper)
   - Provide `<Suspense>` / fallback UI (`ShowcaseFallback` on showcase routes)

3. **DOM + Canvas** (full spec: `.cursor/rules/dom-canvas-layers.mdc`):
   - Site pages: `SiteBackground` → `PageBackgroundCanvas` / `three/backgrounds/*` (fixed, behind)
   - Showcase: route `/portfolio-showcase` — fullscreen Canvas; NO Header/Footer/SiteBackground (`AppChrome` gates chrome)
   - One showcase phase at a time: `loading` | `intro` | `playing`
   - 3D in Canvas only — no CSS “fake 3D” for showcase frames
   - Showcase entry: `ShowcasePrefetchLink`; bypass site boot veil on showcase route

4. **Framer Motion**: `whileInView` + `viewport={{ once: true }}` for scroll; `AnimatePresence` for enter/exit; UI 0.3–0.8s, hero up to ~1.2s.

## Styling
- Tailwind first; theme via CSS vars: `--primary`, `--secondary`, `--accent`, `--dark`, `--dark-card`, `--light`, `--light-muted`
- Gradients: `var(--gradient-hero)` or Tailwind + CSS vars
- **Dark theme only** — do not add light mode

## Naming
- Components: PascalCase · Pages: `page.tsx` · Utils/hooks: camelCase · i18n keys: dot notation (`nav.home`)

## Performance
- Dynamic import heavy 3D/chart/map components (`ssr: false`)
- `next/image` with width/height/alt · `next/font` for Inter
- `useMemo` / `useCallback` in hot R3F paths; never `setState` every frame in `useFrame`

## Backend
- Public reads: `src/lib/supabase.ts` + `src/lib/queries/*`
- Admin writes: `src/lib/supabase-admin.ts` (service role) via `src/actions/admin-*.ts`
- Env helpers: `src/lib/supabase/env.ts`
- Edge functions: `supabase/functions/` — see `supabase/functions/README.md`
- API ownership: `docs/api-ownership.md`

## i18n
- All user-facing copy via `useTranslations()` / server helpers
- Update all 6 locale JSON files for new keys
- Public URL segments stay Croatian (`/proces`, `/o-meni`, `/usluge`, `/kontakt`, `/portfolio-showcase`)
- Language selector: all 6 locales with flag emojis (`src/i18n.ts`)

## Agent memory & env
- Long-term memory: GitHub `ProtosEschatos/Protos-Agent` only (`src/lib/agent-memory.ts`) — no machine filesystem paths in code
- Do **not** touch `.env*` unless the user explicitly asks
- Env reference: `.env.example`

## Git & workflow
- Commit only when the user asks
- Messages: English, imperative — `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `style:`, `chore:`, `docs:`
- One logical change per commit
- Never commit `node_modules/`, `.next/`, `.env*`
- Before push: `npm run lint && npm run type-check && npm run build`
- **Fix, don't remove** working features without explicit user approval (`.cursor/rules/fix-not-remove.mdc`)

## FORBIDDEN
- ❌ Prisma, Convex, Firebase, Vercel CLI, or other backends not in stack
- ❌ Site chrome on `/portfolio-showcase`
- ❌ Multiple simultaneous `fixed inset-0` overlays (site or showcase)
- ❌ GSAP unless user adds it to `package.json`
- ❌ Vanilla Three.js scene setup outside R3F patterns
- ❌ `pages/` router — App Router only
- ❌ CSS modules / styled-components — Tailwind + CSS vars only
- ❌ Light mode
- ❌ New SQL migrations without checking remote Supabase history
- ❌ `any` without strong reason
- ❌ Inline styles when Tailwind suffices
- ❌ Files outside the structure above
- ❌ Deleting user files or `.env*` without explicit approval
- ❌ Broad drive-by refactors or many commits without CI/user checkpoint
